#. <section class="sutta" id="sn6.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn6.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The Appeal"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 6. Brahmalokasutta → pamādasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts2) | pamādaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn6.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Brahmalokasutta"
msgstr "6. The Negligent Brahmā"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.147"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.319"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.6:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā divāvihāragato hoti paṭisallīno."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Buddha had retreated to solitude for the day’s "
"meditation."

#. VAR: paccekaṃ dvārabāhaṃ → paccekadvārabāhaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn6.6:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho subrahmā ca paccekabrahmā suddhāvāso ca paccekabrahmā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā paccekaṃ dvārabāhaṃ upanissāya aṭṭhaṃsu. "
"Atha kho subrahmā paccekabrahmā suddhāvāsaṃ paccekabrahmānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the independent brahmās Subrahmā and Suddhāvāsa went to the Buddha and "
"stationed themselves one by each door-post. Then Subrahmā said to Suddhāvāsa:"

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.4"
msgid "“akālo kho tāva, mārisa, bhagavantaṃ payirupāsituṃ;"
msgstr "“Good sir, it’s the wrong time to pay homage to the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.5"
msgid "divāvihāragato bhagavā paṭisallīno ca."
msgstr "He has retreated into solitude for the day’s meditation."

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.6"
msgid ""
"Asuko ca brahmaloko iddho ceva phīto ca, brahmā ca tatra pamādavihāraṃ "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"But such and such Brahmā realm is successful and prosperous, while the "
"Brahmā living there is negligent."

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.7"
msgid ""
"Āyāma, mārisa, yena so brahmaloko tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ "
"brahmānaṃ saṃvejeyyāmā”ti."
msgstr "Come, let’s go to that Brahmā realm and inspire awe in that Brahmā!”"

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.8"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, mārisā”ti kho suddhāvāso paccekabrahmā subrahmuno paccekabrahmuno "
"paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, good sir,” replied Suddhāvāsa."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.320"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.6:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho subrahmā ca paccekabrahmā suddhāvāso ca paccekabrahmā—seyyathāpi "
"nāma balavā puriso … pe … evameva—bhagavato purato antarahitā tasmiṃ "
"brahmaloke pāturahesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, they "
"vanished from in front of the Buddha and appeared in that Brahmā realm."

msgctxt "sn6.6:2.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho so brahmā te brahmāno dūratova āgacchante. Disvāna te brahmāno "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"That Brahmā saw those Brahmās coming off in the distance and said to them:"

msgctxt "sn6.6:2.3"
msgid "“handa kuto nu tumhe, mārisā, āgacchathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Well now, good sirs, where have you come from?”"

msgctxt "sn6.6:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Āgatā kho mayaṃ, mārisa, amha tassa bhagavato santikā arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"“Good sir, we’ve come from the presence of the Blessed One, the perfected "
"one, the fully awakened Buddha."

# I agree with MS here as opposed to BB, it feels more like a question here, cp. say AN 6.62
msgctxt "sn6.6:2.5"
msgid ""
"Gaccheyyāsi pana tvaṃ, mārisa, tassa bhagavato upaṭṭhānaṃ arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassā”ti?"
msgstr "Shouldn’t you go to attend on that Blessed One?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: Evaṃ vutto → evaṃ vutte (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn6.6:3.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutto, kho so brahmā taṃ vacanaṃ anadhivāsento sahassakkhattuṃ attānaṃ "
"abhinimminitvā subrahmānaṃ paccekabrahmānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When they had spoken, that Brahmā refused to accept their advice. He "
"multiplied himself a thousand times and said to Subrahmā:"

msgctxt "sn6.6:3.2"
msgid "“passasi me no tvaṃ, mārisa, evarūpaṃ iddhānubhāvan”ti?"
msgstr "“Good sir, can’t you see that I have such psychic power?”"

msgctxt "sn6.6:3.3"
msgid "“Passāmi kho tyāhaṃ, mārisa, evarūpaṃ iddhānubhāvan”ti."
msgstr "“I see that, good sir.”"

msgctxt "sn6.6:3.4"
msgid ""
"“So khvāhaṃ, mārisa, evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo kassa aññassa samaṇassa "
"vā brāhmaṇassa vā upaṭṭhānaṃ gamissāmī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Since I have such psychic power and might, what other ascetic or brahmin "
"should I go to and attend upon?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.321"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.6:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho subrahmā paccekabrahmā dvisahassakkhattuṃ attānaṃ abhinimminitvā "
"taṃ brahmānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Subrahmā multiplied himself two thousand times and said to that Brahmā:"

msgctxt "sn6.6:4.2"
msgid "“passasi me no tvaṃ, mārisa, evarūpaṃ iddhānubhāvan”ti?"
msgstr "“Good sir, can’t you see that I have such psychic power?”"

msgctxt "sn6.6:4.3"
msgid "“Passāmi kho tyāhaṃ, mārisa, evarūpaṃ iddhānubhāvan”ti."
msgstr "“I see that, good sir.”"

msgctxt "sn6.6:4.4"
msgid ""
"“Tayā ca kho, mārisa, mayā ca sveva bhagavā mahiddhikataro ceva "
"mahānubhāvataro ca."
msgstr "“That Buddha has even more psychic power and might than you or me."

msgctxt "sn6.6:4.5"
msgid ""
"Gaccheyyāsi tvaṃ, mārisa, tassa bhagavato upaṭṭhānaṃ arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassā”ti?"
msgstr "Shouldn’t you go to attend on that Blessed One?”"

msgctxt "sn6.6:4.6"
msgid "Atha kho so brahmā subrahmānaṃ paccekabrahmānaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then that Brahmā addressed Subrahmā in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.148"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.6:5.1"
msgid "“Tayo supaṇṇā caturo ca haṃsā,"
msgstr ""
"“There are three hundreds of phoenixes, four of swans, and five of eagles."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:5.2"
msgid "Byagghīnisā pañcasatā ca jhāyino;"
msgstr "This palace belongs to him who practiced absorption."

#. <br>
#. VAR: jalate ca → jalati ca (si) | jalateva (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn6.6:5.3"
msgid "Tayidaṃ vimānaṃ jalate ca brahme,"
msgstr "It shines, Brahmā,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:5.4"
msgid "Obhāsayaṃ uttarassaṃ disāyan”ti."
msgstr "lighting up the northern quarter!”"

# Taking jalate here as optative, in the previous as middle active (if it isn’t in fact jalati)
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.322"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.6:6.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi te taṃ jalate vimānaṃ,"
msgstr "“So what if your palace shines,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:6.2"
msgid "Obhāsayaṃ uttarassaṃ disāyaṃ;"
msgstr "lighting up the northern quarter?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:6.3"
msgid "Rūpe raṇaṃ disvā sadā pavedhitaṃ,"
msgstr "A clever person who has seen the deficiency in form,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:6.4"
msgid "Tasmā na rūpe ramatī sumedho”ti."
msgstr "its chronic trembling, takes no pleasure in it.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.6:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho subrahmā ca paccekabrahmā suddhāvāso ca paccekabrahmā taṃ brahmānaṃ "
"saṃvejetvā tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then after inspiring awe in that Brahmā, the independent brahmās Subrahmā "
"and Suddhāvāsa vanished right there."

msgctxt "sn6.6:7.2"
msgid ""
"Agamāsi ca kho so brahmā aparena samayena bhagavato upaṭṭhānaṃ arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassāti."
msgstr "And after some time that Brahmā went to attend on the Buddha."
